LOCUS       SUMO                      98 aa                     UNK 01-JAN-1980
DEFINITION  SUMO (yeast Smt3, S. cerevisiae) — 98-aa ubiquitin-like beta-grasp
            protein ending in the conserved C-terminal diglycine; canonical
            N-terminal SUMO-fusion solubility/expression tag cleaved at the
            Gly-Gly by the SUMO protease Ulp1 to release a native N-terminus..
