                     /note="Small ubiquitin-related modifier (Smt3 / SUMO),
                     Saccharomyces cerevisiae SMT3; UniProt Q12306, residues
                     1–98. Ubiquitin-like (UBL) protein with a beta-grasp fold.
                     As stored this is the mature/processed form retaining the
                     initiator Met (M1) for use as a recombinant N-terminal
                     fusion tag and ending at the conserved C-terminal Gly-Gly
                     (G97-G98), the Ulp1 cleavage site. The full precursor is
                     101 aa; the C-terminal propeptide (residues 99–101, ATY) is
                     removed by the SUMO protease Ulp1 to expose the Gly-Gly.
                     Widely deployed as a SUMO-fusion partner that enhances
                     soluble expression of difficult passengers and, upon Ulp1
                     cleavage at the Gly-Gly, releases the passenger with a
                     native N-terminus."
